599	// AGENTS.md marker-delimited injection. Codex and other harnesses read
600	// AGENTS.md as primary guidance before work; users (and other tools) may
601	// add content of their own. We own only the content between markers —
602	// everything outside is preserved across re-runs of ddx init / ddx update.
603	const (
604		agentsMarkerStart = "<!-- DDX-AGENTS:START -->"
605		agentsMarkerEnd   = "<!-- DDX-AGENTS:END -->"
606	)
607	
608	// ddxAgentsBlock returns the DDx-owned block that gets injected between
609	// markers. Harness-neutral — says "the `ddx` skill", not "/ddx" (which
610	// would only mean something to Claude Code).
611	func ddxAgentsBlock() string {
612		return agentsMarkerStart + `
613	<!-- Managed by ddx init / ddx update. Edit outside these markers. -->
614	
615	# DDx
616	
617	This project uses [DDx](https://github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/ddx) for
618	document-driven development. Use the ` + "`" + `ddx` + "`" + ` skill for beads, work,
619	review, agents, and status — every skills-compatible harness (Claude
620	Code, OpenAI Codex, Gemini CLI, etc.) discovers it from
621	` + "`" + `.claude/skills/ddx/` + "`" + ` and ` + "`" + `.agents/skills/ddx/` + "`" + `.
622	
623	## Default Interactive Mode
624	
625	Broad conversational DDx prompts — queue orientation, planning, review,
626	guidance folding, spec alignment, and bead breakdown — use
627	` + "`" + `interactive-steward` + "`" + ` / ` + "`" + `queue_steward` + "`" + `. Explicit worker commands
628	(` + "`" + `ddx work` + "`" + `, ` + "`" + `ddx try <id>` + "`" + `, "execute bead ` + "`" + `<id>` + "`" + `") route to
629	` + "`" + `bead_execution` + "`" + `. Explicit code/doc edit requests route to
630	` + "`" + `direct_user_implementation` + "`" + `. Explicit review-only requests route to
631	` + "`" + `review` + "`" + `.
632	
633	` + "`" + `DDX_MODE=bead_execution` + "`" + ` overrides only the interactive queue-steward default.
634	It **never** overrides tracker, merge, commit, safety, or verification policy —
635	those apply in every mode.
636	
637	### Mutation policy
638	
639	- **read / plan / fresh-eyes review / fold guidance / align specs** — non-mutating
640	  by default; no tracker writes, no code edits.
641	- **Tracker mutation** (e.g. ` + "`" + `ddx bead create` + "`" + `, ` + "`" + `ddx bead update` + "`" + `) requires an
642	  explicit durable-output verb: "create a bead", "file this as work",
643	  "break down into beads".
644	- **Code edits** require explicit implementation intent ("fix this",
645	  "implement X") or ` + "`" + `bead_execution` + "`" + ` mode.
646	
647	## Files to commit
648	
649	After modifying any of these paths, stage and commit them:
650	
651	- ` + "`" + `.ddx/beads.jsonl` + "`" + ` — work item tracker
652	- ` + "`" + `.ddx/config.yaml` + "`" + ` — project configuration
653	- ` + "`" + `.agents/skills/ddx/` + "`" + ` — the ddx skill (shipped by ddx init)
654	- ` + "`" + `.claude/skills/ddx/` + "`" + ` — same skill, Claude Code location
655	- ` + "`" + `docs/` + "`" + ` — project documentation and artifacts
656	
657	## Conventions
658	
659	- Use ` + "`" + `ddx bead` + "`" + ` for work tracking (not custom issue files).
660	- Documents with ` + "`" + `ddx:` + "`" + ` frontmatter are tracked in the document graph.
661	- Run ` + "`" + `ddx doctor` + "`" + ` to check environment health.
662	- Run ` + "`" + `ddx doc stale` + "`" + ` to find documents needing review.
663	
664	## Merge Policy
665	
666	Branches containing ` + "`" + `ddx try` + "`" + ` or ` + "`" + `ddx work` + "`" + ` commits
667	carry a per-attempt execution audit trail:
668	
669	- ` + "`" + `chore: update tracker (execute-bead <TIMESTAMP>)` + "`" + ` — attempt heartbeats
670	- ` + "`" + `Merge bead <bead-id> attempt <TIMESTAMP>- into <branch>` + "`" + ` — successful lands
671	- ` + "`" + `feat|fix|...: ... [ddx-<id>]` + "`" + ` — substantive bead work
672	
673	Bead records store ` + "`" + `closing_commit_sha` + "`" + ` pointers into this history. Any
674	SHA rewrite breaks the trail. **Never squash, rebase, or filter** these
675	branches. Use only:
676	
677	- ` + "`" + `git merge --ff-only` + "`" + ` when the target is a strict ancestor, or
678	- ` + "`" + `git merge --no-ff` + "`" + ` when divergence exists
679	
680	Forbidden on execute-bead branches: ` + "`" + `gh pr merge --squash` + "`" + `,
681	` + "`" + `gh pr merge --rebase` + "`" + `, ` + "`" + `git rebase -i` + "`" + ` with fixup/squash/drop,
682	` + "`" + `git filter-branch` + "`" + `, ` + "`" + `git filter-repo` + "`" + `, and ` + "`" + `git commit --amend` + "`" + ` on
683	any commit already in the trail.
684	` + agentsMarkerEnd + "\n"
685	}
